				<div id="disp-quote" class="category-header clearfix">
					<hgroup class="no-margin">
						<h3><a href="artist/Snoop-Dogg/41625">Famous lyrics by&nbsp;&raquo;</a></h3>
					</hgroup>
					
        				<div id="featured-artist-avatar" data-artist="Snoop Dogg" data-img="1"><img src="https://encrypted-tbn1.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTKUMjGCsmwKxTtPwUwe95stioH7pWmRbET_tdI5n9PJeK8kHirpYvnPx8" class="artist-thumb"></div>
        				
        				<div id="artist-bio-ext">
                        <div class="hidden-xs">
        						<div style="position:relative;float:right;top:0px;right:0px"><div class="fb-like" data-href="" data-width="" data-height="" data-colorscheme="light" data-layout="button_count" data-action="like" data-show-faces="true" data-send="false"></div></div>        						<h1 class="artist"><a href="artist/Snoop-Dogg/41625">Snoop Dogg</a></h1>
        					</div>
        					<p class="artist hidden-sm hidden-md hidden-lg"><a href="artist/Snoop-Dogg/41625">Snoop Dogg</a></p>
        												<p class="artist-bio">Calvin Cordozar Broadus, Jr. (born October 20, 1971) is an American rapper, singer-songwriter, record producer, and actor, well known by his alter-egos Snoop Doggy Dogg, Snoop Dogg and Snoop Lion. Snoop Lion has sold over 30 million albums worldwide. His music career began in 1992 when he was discovered by Dr. Dre. He collaborated on Dre's solo debut The Chronic, and on the theme song to the film Deep Cover. Snoop's debut album Doggystyle, was released in 1993 under Death Row Records, debuting at No.1 on both the Billboard 200 and R&amp;B charts. Selling almost a million copies in the first week of its release, Doggystyle became certified 4× platinum in 1994 and spawned several hit singles, including "What's My Name" and "Gin &amp; Juice". In 1994, Snoop released a soundtrack on Death Row Records for the short film Murder Was The Case, starring himself. His second album Tha Doggfather (1996), also debuted at No.1 on both charts with "Snoop's Upside Ya Head" as the lead single. The album was certified double platinum in 1997.</p>
							<p class="artist-bio-link">
								<a href="addbio.php?aid=41625">Update this biography &raquo;</a><br>
								<a href="https://www.biographies.net/people/en/snoop_dogg">Complete biography of Snoop Dogg &raquo;</a>
							</p>
